No dawb of elegiac strain These holy walls shall ever stain ; As spiders Irish wainscot flee , Falsehood with them shall disagree : This floor let not the vulgar tread , Who worship only what they dread ; Nor bigots who but one way see Through blinkers of authority ; Nor they who its four saints defame By making virtue but a name ; Nor abstract wit , ( painful regale To hunt the pig with slippery tail ! )
